Now that the event has concluded and the results are being tabulated I have one thing to say; Thank you. Thank you to my husband and kids. Thank you @themisterladd for letting me have my marathon. ✨Special note✨I know you might find these “Ginger Ladd’s Adventures,” silly…and that’s the point. I’ve made six of these this last year, and I find myself making them when social media becomes redundant to me. I’m not trying to sell you something…impress…or persuade…I’m just having fun… And I think that has gotten lost on most social media posts… Love you Dolls.
Episode 75 of Ginger Ladd’s Adventures is out!  He was boned to be wild! 
This gothic skeleton has a bone to pick with you…. and he isn’t afraid to use it. Your teeth will chatter and… your bones will rattle. You’ve never seen so much Boning… and in the end it might just crack you wide open!

Its 1669 Paris, France and Monsieur Ladd reemerges from the family crypt. He’s starved to the bone but it isn’t food that will satiate his voracious appetite. Luring the Parisian nobility to his palatial estate is easy, and once ensnared, the boning never stops. 
Spines shiver.
Hipbones quiver.
And you thought the femur was the biggest human bone!

The critically reviewed, limited reality series will leave you starving for more and by the end, your skull just may shatter with desire. Follow Ginger Ladd  for more, and remember, He was boned to be wild!

“I don’t know when, I don’t know how But I know something’s starting right now
Watch and you’ll see, someday I’II be Part of your world...” My family and I have marched in the local #rockawaynyc #poseidonsparade for the last 3 years...but we made the decision not to attend what would have been our fourth year. It’s painful to participate in something where you and your family are villified for being authentic. Not by everyone of course, but it’s time to not only protect my heart but my family from the taunts, threats, and exclusion. I hope someday we can return to something that brings so many others joy... in the meantime...
It’s much safer for us to swim on our own.

Living in Rockaway Beach, NY and Navigating Threats, Discrimination, & Community.

We love our life here in The Rockaways (New York, New York), but things have changed for us over the last four to five years. 
While this community is filled with wonderful, kind, compassionate people, it is also filled with people that have personally threatened me and my family. 
Whether it’s been overt or passive, our biracial queer family has received a lot of hate, and it’s something that we’ve kept quiet until now. 
Not all of our experiences have been bad here. In fact, most have been good, but if YOU have a story of being targeted or discriminated against because of gender, identity, religion, sex, sexual orientation, the color of your skin... Contact me at contact@GingerLadd.com  I would like to hear your story. Remember, together we can do amazing things.

At the end of the day, it’s an amazing, caring community with so much to offer. It’s up to us to show that hate and ignorance have no place in The Rockaways.

#rockawaybeach #nylove #rockawaybeachnyc #rockawayslife #threateningtimes #compassionatecommunity #lifeschallenges #kindnessmatters #safetyfirst

✨I’m fine.✨This is me the LAST time I was jumped and beaten for being me…and I never told you. I didn’t go to the police. They were never held accountable. Don’t victim shame me… I was just too scared. This spiralled me into a deep depression because I internalized their hate and shame. But I’m not scared anymore. And I won’t be silent again. ✨Recently I posted why my family would not attend a local event 🌊🧜🏻‍♀️🧜🏻‍♂️ in The Rockaways. The threats we received outweighed our desire to attend. The outpouring of love and understanding we received was beautiful as most of you understood, but some surprised us by saying our fear reflected poorly on their event. No. I refuse to allow you to shame us for being careful. This was never about you. We gladly paid every year to attend, to advertise, donated money, and promoted your event. You can block us on social media… but I hope you see this and finally understand. If someone tells you they fear for their life… believe them. #gingerladd #themisterladd #gaybashingisreal #thegingerladd #victimblaming

In 2023, my life as an entertainer has been reshaped by the challenges my family faces. 
We yearn for the days of supporting and attending outdoor festivals and parades, but amidst it all, a harsh reality confronts us, the real presence of death threats. 
I wear my hats as entertainer, husband, father, and a son caring for my elderly mother alongside my husband. 
The weight of knowing that if something were to happen to us, it would be utterly devastating. 
I wish I could convey the sheer terror of living under the constant shadow of violence, especially during events that should be celebrations. But at the same time, I wouldn’t wish this fear upon anyone, for it’s a pain and anxiety that’s indescribable. 
Currently, there are over 540 anti LGBTQIA+ bills that have been introduced in state legislatures, a record, as reported by The Human Rights Campaign (HRC) @humanrightscampaign these bills aim to strip away our fundamental rights, the right to simply exist. 

We are not asking for special treatment. We are simply fighting to survive. 
Please help us by liking & sharing this post.
Thank you.
